narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It is a great seminar. Take it!
If you are interested in colonialism, definitely!

Definitely take this seminar if you are at all interested in colonialism! Daniel was a great professor - chill and lead good discussions. The readings can be kind of long but seriously, they are all really interesting. Not too much work either, its completely worth it!

I absolutely recommend this course. One of the best seminars I've taken. The readings are interesting, the discussions are great, and you learn a ton. The papers are pretty standard, and can be fun if you're into them. I didn't think I was that interested in studying colonialism, but I was totally drawn in by the readings, so writing the paper was easy! The readings aren't small every week, but it's totally worth it to do all of them, and the responses aren't that difficult.
